    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-sap-build-apps-delete-item-persistent-storage/qaq-p/13983363/comment-id/4898730#M4898730</id>
    <title>Re: SAP Build Apps - Delete Item Persistent Storage</title>
    <updated>2025-01-12T08:04:00.893000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/1925878"&gt;@Paull1&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;It can be a little confusing how they implemented it.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;First, no matter what you define as your fields for on-device storage, you can create a record with whatever you want. The definition you create for your entity is for defining a schema in your app, but the "storage" on your device is not validating what you send it against this schema. It is not like a database.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Second, the ID field is auto generated behind the scenes by Build Apps when you create a record on device. So you could delete the ID field from the schema, it will still be generated. And you do not get this field in the create record because you do not need to generate it.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-sap-build-apps-delete-item-persistent-storage/qaq-p/13983363/comment-id/4898730#M4898730"/>
    <published>2025-01-12T08:04:00.893000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
