  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-blog-posts/understand-dms-api-free-postman-collection/bc-p/13985137#M435</id>
    <title>Re: Understand DMS API – Free Postman Collection!!</title>
    <updated>2025-01-14T12:51:07.221000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Also note that some APIs require the objectId and some require the path.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;H3 id="toc-hId-1208505728"&gt;Path&lt;/H3&gt;&lt;P&gt;When creating a document, you provide the path (in the URL path) to the folder where you want the document created, as in the &lt;A href="https://api.sap.com/api/CreateDocumentApi/path/post_browser__repository_id__root" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;Create Document&lt;/A&gt; API.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;H3 id="toc-hId-1011992223"&gt;ObjectId&lt;/H3&gt;&lt;P&gt;When listing the child objects of a specific object, you supply the object ID, like &lt;A href="https://api.sap.com/api/GetChildrenApi/path/get_browser__repository_id__root" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;Get Children&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;API, or when deleting an object with the&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://api.sap.com/api/DeleteObjectApi/resource/Delete_Object" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;Delete Object&lt;/A&gt; API.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1736855451102.png" style="width: 920px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/211727iEB1CCCA6F12A2F08/image-dimensions/920x474?v=v2" width="920" height="474" role="button" title="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1736855451102.png" alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1736855451102.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;H3 id="toc-hId-815478718"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/H3&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-blog-posts/understand-dms-api-free-postman-collection/bc-p/13985137#M435"/>
    <published>2025-01-14T12:51:07.221000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-blogs-by-sap/connect-sap-build-apps-with-dms-free-projects-videos/ba-p/13986096</id>
    <title>Connect SAP Build Apps with DMS (FREE projects/videos)</title>
    <updated>2025-01-15T07:28:08.418000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;I've created 3 new short videos to show you how to work with DMS from within your SAP Build Apps project. I've also released a demo app (both skeleton and complete versions) that lets a user navigate through DMS, create folders, upload documents, and delete documents.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&lt;H4 id="toc-hId-1337617462"&gt;Video #1:&amp;nbsp;#Set Up SAP Build Apps to Work With DMS&lt;/H4&gt;&lt;P&gt;Set up the destination to DMS, add it o your project, and create a data variable with the schema for most DMS API responses.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;div class="video-embed-center video-embed"&gt;&lt;iframe class="embedly-embed" src="https://cdn.embedly.com/widgets/media.html?src=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FlhBB2mM9Nho%3Ffeature%3Doembed&amp;amp;display_name=YouTube&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DlhBB2mM9Nho&amp;amp;image=https%3A%2F%2Fi.ytimg.com%2Fvi%2FlhBB2mM9Nho%2Fhqdefault.jpg&amp;amp;type=text%2Fhtml&amp;amp;schema=youtube" width="200" height="112" scrolling="no" title="Set Up SAP Build Apps to Work With DMS" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture;" allowfullscreen="true"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&lt;H4 id="toc-hId-1141103957"&gt;Videos #2: Call DMS from SAP Build App&lt;/H4&gt;&lt;P&gt;Use the HTTP Destination Request flow function to list objects in the root or any folder, and navigate the DMS tree.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;div class="video-embed-center video-embed"&gt;&lt;iframe class="embedly-embed" src="https://cdn.embedly.com/widgets/media.html?src=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FSJt_BzctwbI%3Ffeature%3Doembed&amp;amp;display_name=YouTube&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DSJt_BzctwbI&amp;amp;image=https%3A%2F%2Fi.ytimg.com%2Fvi%2FSJt_BzctwbI%2Fhqdefault.jpg&amp;amp;type=text%2Fhtml&amp;amp;schema=youtube" width="200" height="112" scrolling="no" title="Call DMS from SAP Build Apps" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture;" allowfullscreen="true"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&lt;H4 id="toc-hId-944590452"&gt;Video #3: Upload a File from Build Apps to DMS&lt;/H4&gt;&lt;P&gt;Use the new flow function to upload binary files to DMS, as well as to delete files.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;div class="video-embed-center video-embed"&gt;&lt;iframe class="embedly-embed" src="https://cdn.embedly.com/widgets/media.html?src=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FgIW_tHOaNuY%3Ffeature%3Doembed&amp;amp;display_name=YouTube&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DgIW_tHOaNuY&amp;amp;image=https%3A%2F%2Fi.ytimg.com%2Fvi%2FgIW_tHOaNuY%2Fhqdefault.jpg&amp;amp;type=text%2Fhtml&amp;amp;schema=youtube" width="169" height="95" scrolling="no" title="Upload a File from Build Apps to DMS" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture;" allowfullscreen="true"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&lt;H4 id="toc-hId-748076947"&gt;DMS Playlist&lt;/H4&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Learning DMS? It might help to go through the &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;A href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL6RpkC85SLQCsKSvIOqMzFKW30B4TKXh-" target="_self" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;SAP Document Management Service playlist&lt;/A&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;, including the 3 TechBytes on DMS Integration Option, Application Option and Repository Option.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1736919128877.png" style="width: 660px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/212026iD08AB6072D163EF5/image-dimensions/660x432?v=v2" width="660" height="432" role="button" title="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1736919128877.png" alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1736919128877.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;All of these videos are based off the amazing work by Ming Kho (&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/39325"&gt;@mingkho&lt;/a&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;), who not only developed the new HTTP Destination Request flow function that enables binary uploads, but patiently and clearly helped me understand how to use it.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;H2 id="toc-hId-293398004"&gt;New HTTP Destination Request Flow Function&lt;/H2&gt;&lt;P&gt;The new flow function lets you define multipart HTTP calls, especially so you can upload binary files, AND use a destination to define the connection details .&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="httpflowfunction-transparent.png" style="width: 344px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/212032i0836C5BAB0A2419A/image-dimensions/344x123?v=v2" width="344" height="123" role="button" title="httpflowfunction-transparent.png" alt="httpflowfunction-transparent.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The flow function lets you have greater control over your HTTP calls while using a destination, and in a form i is easier to set. You can set:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Destination&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;HTTP method&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Request body type&lt;/STRONG&gt; – json, x-www-form-urlencoded, multipart/form-data, binary&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Request body&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Path&lt;/STRONG&gt; (this was quite helpful to be able to provide a path here)&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Headers&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="httppropertiespost.png" style="width: 212px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/212033i26FA6B67885DCECE/image-dimensions/212x393?v=v2" width="212" height="393" role="button" title="httppropertiespost.png" alt="httppropertiespost.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Though in my sample app I only really needed this flow function for uploading files, I used it for all my calls. Even for the other calls it helped having the &lt;STRONG&gt;Path&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;property.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;H2 id="toc-hId-96884499"&gt;Download Skeleton/Complete App&lt;/H2&gt;&lt;P&gt;I have provided an app that lets the user navigate the DMS tree, create folders, upload documents, and delete documents.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="app.png" style="width: 798px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/212088i8E9FFD8881EC79C2/image-dimensions/798x388?v=v2" width="798" height="388" role="button" title="app.png" alt="app.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Besides DMS, some other things you can learn from the app are:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Creating and triggering events&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Conditional formatting of styles&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Conditional formatting of icons&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Creating variables with schema based on API response&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P&gt;There are 2 version of the app:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;A href="https://github.com/sap-tutorials/sap-build-apps/blob/main/projects/dms/DMS%20From%20BuildApps%20-%20Template.mtar" target="_self" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;Skeleton App&lt;/A&gt; (to follow along starting from video #1)&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;A href="https://github.com/sap-tutorials/sap-build-apps/blob/main/projects/dms/DMS%20From%20BuildApps%20-%20Complete.mtar" target="_self" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;Complete App&lt;/A&gt;, ready to use.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P&gt;For the complete app to work, you may need to set the destination in the HTTP Destination Request flow functions (there are 4 of them throughout the app).&lt;/P&gt;&lt;H2 id="toc-hId--99629006"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/H2&gt;&lt;H2 id="toc-hId--296142511"&gt;DMS APS&lt;/H2&gt;&lt;P&gt;The documentation for the DMS APIs are located here:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;A href="https://api.sap.com/package/SAPDocumentManagementServiceIntegrationOptionCMISAPI/overview" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;SAP Document Management Service, Integration Option - CMIS&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;A href="https://api.sap.com/package/SAPDocumentManagementServiceIntegrationOption/rest" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;SAP Document Management Service, Integration Option (non-CMIS)&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-blogs-by-sap/connect-sap-build-apps-with-dms-free-projects-videos/ba-p/13986096"/>
    <published>2025-01-15T07:28:08.418000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-blog-posts/3-more-videos-on-integrating-sap-build-apps-with-dms/ba-p/13990976</id>
    <title>3 more videos on integrating SAP Build Apps with DMS</title>
    <updated>2025-01-20T14:54:16.778000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;I wrote a blog about integrating Document Management Service (DMS) with SAP Build Apps, which I think will be especially helpful for those of you working on apps that involve document management.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;A href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-blogs-by-sap/connect-sap-build-apps-with-dms-free-projects-videos/ba-p/13986096" target="_blank"&gt;https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-blogs-by-sap/connect-sap-build-apps-with-dms-free-projects-videos/ba-p/13986096&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="2MinutesOf-thumbnail-horizontal-dms3.jpg" style="width: 793px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/214442i5147F9BD9BD25A2E/image-dimensions/793x446?v=v2" width="793" height="446" role="button" title="2MinutesOf-thumbnail-horizontal-dms3.jpg" alt="2MinutesOf-thumbnail-horizontal-dms3.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The blog includes:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Free project&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Links to 3 new videos showing how to connect with DMS using the new HTTP Destination Request flow function, including with the help of the free project&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Additional tips on DMS and on using the new flow function&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P&gt;I’d love to hear how you’re using DMS in your own SAP Build Apps projects or any feedback you have. Feel free to join the conversation here or on the blog!&lt;/P&gt;</content>
